                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Damm</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales, Ariz</hi>
                        </placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-13T23:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 13, 1929—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 14—3:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From Bursley:</p>
                <p>Extremely important for you and Department, April 13, 10 p.m. Very urgent and
                    strictly confidential.</p>
                <pb facs="0513" n="395" xml:id="pg_395"/>
                <p>Southern Pacific Company has suspended operations creating a dangerous situation
                    and eleven American employees now taking refuge in the Consulate. Railway does
                    not know destination of about six thousand rebel troops southbound but assumes
                    Guaymas or points south. We cannot communicate with destroyer until tomorrow
                    morning, if then. A destroyer needed Guaymas at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Damm</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
